    <question>
        <prompt>The Harlem Renaissance writers demonstrated diversity through:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Uniform writing styles</option>
            <option letter="b">Different approaches to expressing Black experience</option>
            <option letter="c">Avoiding racial themes</option>
            <option letter="d">Political uniformity</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Harlem Renaissance writers demonstrated diversity through their varied approaches to expressing African American experience. Writers like Langston Hughes embraced vernacular language and jazz rhythms, while Countee Cullen used traditional poetic forms. Claude McKay combined militant themes with classical sonnets. These different approaches reflected various perspectives on how to best express Black identity and experience in literature.</explanation>
    </question>
